WorkItem.Description:
How to reproduce the bug:
	1. Create DataGrid with manually defined columns
	2. Define validation rules for cells and rows
	3. Change a cell creating a validation error
	4. Now change ItemsSource to a valid collection without any validation errors
	5. Grid resets, but disallows any editing.

Similar issue is discussed here: http://wpf.codeplex.com/Thread/View.aspx?ThreadId=70620

Workaround adapted from http://maximusmahender.spaces.live.com/blog/cns!E5ADEF9F25580ADA!237.entry?sa=535108261
 
        public void ResetDatagrid()
        {
            Type DatagridType = fieldsTable.GetType();
            PropertyInfo HasCellValidationProperty = DatagridType.GetProperty("HasCellValidationError", BindingFlags.NonPublic | BindingFlags.Instance);
 
            if (HasCellValidationProperty != null)
            {
                HasCellValidationProperty.SetValue(fieldsTable, false, null);
            }
 
        }
